  "texts": [
    "Galhardi and Brancher (2018) conducted a systematic literature review on automated short answer grading (ASAG) using classical machine learning approaches.",
    "The survey encompasses various topics such as feature selection, natural language processing and the application of machine learning in ASAG.",
    "In a related study, Haller et al. (2022) conducted a complementary survey to classical machine learning approaches, focusing on deep learning-based models and representation learning techniques.",
    "The survey delves into papers that introduce ASAG utilizing word embeddings, sequential and attention-based models.",
    "It is important to note that these surveys primarily focus on ASAG research, which differs from essay scoring as it involves the utilization of a reference answer for score calculation."
